SIMPLE: thrift
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thrift
<hw>Thrift</hw> <pr>(thr⟦icr⟧ft)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧rift</ets>. See <er>Thrive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
thriving state; good husbandry; economical management in regard to
property; frugality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rest, . . . willing to fall to <qex>thrift</qex>, prove very
good husbands.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Success and advance in the acquisition of property;
increase of worldly goods; gain; prosperity.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Your
<xex>thrift</xex> is gone full clean.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a mind presages me such <qex>thrift</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1503 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Vigorous growth, as of a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of several species of
flowering plants of the genera <gen>Statice</gen> and
<gen>Armeria</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Common thrift</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd><spn>Armeria vulgaris</spn>; -- also called <altname>sea
pink</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Frugality; economy; prosperity; gain;
profit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thriftily</ent>⟦br⟧
